cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on extending the abilities of service robots in everyday manipulation tasks, and proposes a method to identify anomalies during manipulation episodes. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method uses Long Short-Term Memories (LSTM) to fuse sensory modalities and classify anomalies in real-time, which falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The sensory modalities used in the proposed method include visual observations, which suggests the involvement of computer vision techniques. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper compares the proposed LSTM-based method with Hidden Markov Models (HMMs) and Conditional Random Fields (CRFs), which are machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper emphasizes the importance of robots being able to identify what they cannot achieve in certain cases, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction.
